#----- Improved Uncanny Dodge

base quality Improved Uncanny Dodge =

  type              Extraordinary;
  worlds            Generic;
  references        WTC 17724: 50;
  description
  "The character can no longer be flanked; she can react to opponents on
  opposite sides of her as easily as she can react to a single attacker. This
  defense denies a \Class{rogue} the ability to sneak attack the character by
  flanking her, unless the attacker has at least four more \Class{rogue} levels
  than the target does.

  If a character already has uncanny dodge (see above) from a second class, the
  character automatically gains improved uncanny dodge instead, and the levels
  from the classes that grant uncanny dodge stack to determine the minimum
  \Class{rogue} level required to flank the character.";
  short description "Cannot be flanked anymore (unless high level).";
  synonyms          "Uncanny Dodge, Improved",
                    "Dodge, Uncanny Improved";
  categories        option.

